<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="considerate-adj">considerate <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /kən'sɪdərət/    美 /kən'sɪdərət/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-thoughtful">1.★ <strong>体贴的；体谅他人的；考虑周到的(thoughtful)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He is <strong>considerate of / to / toward</strong> old people. 
他对老人很体贴。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It was</strong> very <strong>considerate of</strong> you to let us know you were going to be late<strong>to_1</strong>
你告知我们你会迟到，真是考虑周到。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>considerately /kən'sɪdərətli/ adv   </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>It was considerate <strong><em>_</em></strong> Michael to inform us of his delay in case we got worried.   （2015 福建改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. of  </p></div>